dcterms:description: International prices for cotton, represented by the Cotton A index, which corresponds to the average of the cheapest five quotations among eighteen varieties of upland cotton traded internationally.
dcterms:title: Cotton price (Cotton A index)

dcterms:description: International prices for oil, represented by the average spot price of Brent, Dubai, and West Texas Intermediate, the three leading indices representing the market.
dcterms:title: Oil price (average spot price of Brent, Dubai, and West Texas Intermediate)

dcterms:description: A dataset containing international commodity prices, used for forecasting purposes in economic models.
dcterms:title: World Bank commodity prices dataset
